## Technologies Used

- Front-end: Vue.js, HTML, CSS
- Back-end: Java, Spring Boot, MySQL
- Database: MySQL
- HTTP Client: Axios

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js (https://nodejs.org)
- Java Development Kit (JDK) (https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/javase-jdk11-downloads.html)
- MySQL Server (https://www.mysql.com)

### Installation

1. Clone the repository: `git clone https://github.com/IlmarIlves/kassas-steem.git`
2. Change to the project directory: `cd kassasusteem`
3. Install the front-end dependencies in client: `npm install`
4. Add local machine server url, password & username configurations to application.properties,
5. Run command in project root server direcotry: `.\gradlew.bat bootRun`
6. Start the front-end development server: Run `npm run dev` in the project root directory.
7. Access the application: Open your web browser and navigate to the ip result of the previous command

## Usage

- Add new baking items by providing a name and the associated ingredients.
- View the list of baking items on the home page.
- Click on a baking item to view its details, including the ingredients.
- Use the search bar to search for specific baking items.
- Use the filters to refine the displayed baking items based on quantity, name, or other criteria.
- Click on the column headers in the baking list to sort the items in ascending or descending order.

